FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1775754356
OL,3,CFacebook worker faces criminal probe
OL,4,Cfor 'downloading 30,000 private
OL,5,Cpictures'
OL,7,FFacebook suffered a bug in 2018 which
OL,8,Fwas believed to have affected up to
OL,9,F6.8 million people and given third-
OL,10,Fparty apps wider access to user photos
OL,11,Fon the social network.
OL,13,FIn 2024, it was reported that Meta had
OL,14,Fbeen fined 91 million euro by the Data
OL,15,FProtection Commission in Ireland over
OL,16,Fthe way millions of Facebook and
OL,17,FInstagram user passwords had been
OL,18,Finadvertently stored in plaintext on
OL,19,Fits internal systems, meaning they
OL,20,Fwere not protected by encryption.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1775754356
OL,3,CFacebook worker faces criminal probe
OL,4,Cfor 'downloading 30,000 private
OL,5,Cpictures'
OL,7,FThe latest security concern has
OL,8,Femerged just after Meta, which also
OL,9,Fowns WhatsApp, suffered a landmark
OL,10,Fcourt defeat alongside Google last
OL,11,Fmonth after being accused of failing
OL,12,Fto protect its users from harm.
OL,14,FA court in Los Angeles found the
OL,15,Fcompanies liable for a woman's
OL,16,Fchildhood social media addiction in a
OL,17,Fruling which could have widespread
OL,18,Framifications for the way the
OL,19,Fplatforms are operated in the future.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1775754356
OL,3,CFacebook worker faces criminal probe
OL,4,Cfor 'downloading 30,000 private
OL,5,Cpictures'
OL,7,FJon Baines, senior data protection
OL,8,Fspecialist at law firm Mishcon de
OL,9,FReya, said: "When an employee accesses
OL,10,Fpersonal data, such as images of
OL,11,Fcustomers, without the employer's
OL,12,Fauthorisation, there is the potential
OL,13,Ffor offences under data protection and
OL,14,Fcomputer misuse laws to be committed
OL,15,Fby that employee.
OL,26,@qD@MOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1775754356
OL,3,CFacebook worker faces criminal probe
OL,4,Cfor 'downloading 30,000 private
OL,5,Cpictures'
OL,7,F"The general approach will be that,
OL,8,Fprovided the employer ` here, Meta `
OL,9,Fhas appropriate technical and
OL,10,Forganisational measures in place to
OL,11,Fprevent, or at least detect, the
OL,12,Funauthorised access, it will not
OL,13,Fitself be liable: the law doesn't seek
OL,14,Fto punish responsible organisations
OL,15,Ffor the actions of rogue employees.
OL,26,@oD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1775754356
OL,3,CFacebook worker faces criminal probe
OL,4,Cfor 'downloading 30,000 private
OL,5,Cpictures'
OL,7,F"That said, if the Information
OL,8,FCommissioner ` or a court ` were to
OL,9,Fdecide that Meta had not had
OL,10,Fappropriate technical and
OL,11,Forganisational measures in place to
OL,12,Fprotect customer data, then Meta (or
OL,13,Fanother organisation in similar
OL,14,Fcircumstances) might potentially be
OL,15,Fliable to significant fines, or to
OL,16,Flegal claims for damages."
OL,26,@oD@AOUxD@ZO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40911
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1775754356
OL,3,CFacebook worker faces criminal probe
OL,4,Cfor 'downloading 30,000 private
OL,5,Cpictures'
OL,7,FA spokesperson for the Information
OL,8,FCommissioner's Office (ICO) said: "We
OL,9,Fare aware of this incident. The ICO
OL,10,Fregularly engages with social media
OL,11,Fplatforms, including Meta, regarding
OL,12,Fapproaches to data protection to
OL,13,Fensure that users rights and freedoms
OL,14,Fare being upheld.
OL,16,F"Social media users should be able to
OL,17,Ftrust that their personal information
OL,18,Fis handled responsibly."
OL,26,@pD@cOUxD@AOUzD@XO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/12
